  "pages": [
    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "James MCFARLAND, manager of\nthe western division Of Pinkerton's\ndetective agency, who has achieved\nconsiderable newspaper notoriety\nby arresting President Meyer and\nSecretary Haywood of the Western\nFederation Of Miners, is in Spo-\nkane. He will leave tomorrow for\nBoise, Idaho.\n\n\nMr.. MCFARLAND has worked for\nthree generations Of the Pinker-\ntons and during that time has\nhandled some great cases; but\nnone of them, as he admits, have\never assumed the magnitude of the\nSteunenberg case. A Press repre-\nsentative asked him as to his age\nthis morning and he was as reti-\ncent as an old maid, saying only\nthat he was old enough to vote."
    }
  ]
